# Branding + theming packages from the [genesi] repo. Without these the
# live ISO ships without /usr/share/genesi/skel-override, the Welcome app,
# Calamares branding, etc. — shellprocess@copy_genesi has no source to
# copy from and the installed system ends up vanilla Plasma.
genesi-settings
genesi-calamares-branding
genesi-welcome
genesi-ai-mode
# MemPalace integration (scripts + per-user indexer/bridge services only — the
# mempalace CLI is provisioned per-user at runtime, so this adds negligible
# squashfs weight, unlike genesi-llama-cpp below). Lets the live ISO demo the
# AI long-term memory + prompt-cache bridge.
genesi-mempalace
genesi-packageinstaller
genesi-kde-settings
# NOTE: genesi-llama-cpp (Vulkan llama.cpp + Vulkan libs, tens of MB) and the
# genesi-desktop meta are deliberately NOT on the live ISO — they belong on the
# INSTALLED system (netinstall) only. On the live medium they just bloat the
# squashfs, which is what makes the "Load to RAM" (copytoram=y) boot entry OOM
# on low-RAM VMs. llama.cpp also needs models the live ISO doesn't carry, and
# the meta would drag the entire installed-system component set onto the image.
