# NVIDIA: the live ISO deliberately does NOT ship the prebuilt nvidia-open
# kernel modules (linux-cachyos[-lts]-nvidia-open). Those hard-pin an EXACT
# nvidia-utils version (e.g. =610.43.02); CachyOS is rolling, so whenever the
# module package and nvidia-utils fall out of sync on the mirror the ENTIRE ISO
# pacstrap dies with "unable to satisfy dependency 'nvidia-utils=X' required by
# linux-cachyos-nvidia-open" (hit 2026-05-31 and again 2026-06-05). The
# live/installer environment only needs a working display, which nouveau
# (in-kernel, no version pin) provides on every GPU. The proper open/proprietary
# driver is installed on the TARGET by chwd during install
# (shellprocess@genesi_gpu in the calamares config). Result: nvidia version
# churn can never break the ISO build again.
linux-cachyos-lts
linux-cachyos
